def plotScatterMatrix(df, plotSize, textSize):
    df = df.select_dtypes(include=[np.number]) # keep only numerical columns
    # Remove rows and columns that would lead to df being singular
    df = df.dropna(axis='columns')
    df = df[[col for col in df if df[col].nunique() > 1]] # keep columns where there are more than 1 unique values
    columnNames = list(df)
    if len(columnNames) > 10: # reduce the number of columns for matrix inversion of kernel density plots
        columnNames = columnNames[:10]
    df = df[columnNames]
    ax = pd.plotting.scatter_matrix(df, alpha=0.75, figsize=[plotSize, plotSize], diagonal='kde')

    corrs = df.corr().values
    for i, j in zip(*plt.np.triu_indices_from(ax, k = 1)):
        ax[i, j].annotate('Corr. coef = %.3f' % corrs[i, j], (0.8, 0.2), xycoords='axes fraction', ha='center', va='center', size=textSize)
    plt.suptitle('Correlation Plot')
    plt.show()

plotScatterMatrix(df, 20, 0)

Find best Classifier¶

In [ ]:
X = df[features]
y = df[target]

X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, train_size=0.5, shuffle=True)

# scale
sc_X = StandardScaler()
X_train = sc_X.fit_transform(X_train)
X_test = sc_X.transform(X_test)


clf = LogisticRegression(max_iter=1000)
clf.fit(X_train, y_train)

yhat_train = clf.predict(X_train)
yhat_test = clf.predict(X_test)

classifiers = {
    'Logistic Regression': LogisticRegression(max_iter=1000),
    'Decision Tree': DecisionTreeClassifier(),
    'Random Forest': RandomForestClassifier(),
    'K-Nearest Neighbors': KNeighborsClassifier()
}

results = {
    'classifier': [],
    'accuracy_train': [],
    'accuracy_test': []
}

for clf_name, clf in classifiers.items():
    clf.fit(X_train, y_train)
    yhat_train = clf.predict(X_train)
    yhat_test = clf.predict(X_test)
    
    results['classifier'].append(clf_name)
    results['accuracy_train'].append(accuracy_score(y_train, yhat_train))
    results['accuracy_test'].append(accuracy_score(y_test, yhat_test))

# Ausgabe der Ergebnisse
for i in range(len(results['classifier'])):
    print("Classifier:", results['classifier'][i])
    print("Train Accuracy:", results['accuracy_train'][i])
    print("Test Accuracy:", results['accuracy_test'][i])
    print("---------------------")
